Use istanbul/lib/cli.js instead of node_modules/.bin/istanbul
Fixes #1331
Due to the way, "bin"-files are distributed into the node_modules/.bin directory on Windows, the task "test:cov" did not work on Windows. This commit uses the node-script directly.

Force LF line-endings for spec/artifacts

Handlebars.compile() does not modify "options" anymore
Fixes #1327
- This commit creates a shallow copy of the "options" passed to Handlebars.compile() in order to prevent modifications - Note that "new Handlebars.Compiler().compile(..., options)" still modify the options object. This might change in the future, if anybody needs a fix for that.
fixup (add coverage report as build artifact)

Gracefully handle missing uglify-js dependency
closes #1391
uglify-js is an optional dependency and should be treated as such. This commit gracefully handles MODULE_NOT_FOUND errors while loading uglify.

Several refactorings
- Check for existing uglify-js (and load uglify-js) only if minification was activated - Use "require.resolve" to check if uglify exists. Otherwise, a missing dependency of uglify-js would cause the same behavior as missing uglify-js. (Only a warning, no error) - Refactor tests to mock Module._resolveFilename, because mocking only Module.prototype.resolve() does not affect 'require.resolve' - Some cleanups (remove obsolete comments and empty lines)

Put minification into a single function.
The code is better to read like this, with all minification-lines being together.

Gracefully handle missing uglify-js dependency
closes #1391
uglify-js is an optional dependency and should be treated as such. This commit gracefully handles MODULE_NOT_FOUND errors while loading uglify.
- Check for existing uglify-js (and load uglify-js) only if minification was activated - Use "require.resolve" to check if uglify exists. Otherwise, a missing dependency of uglify-js would cause the same behavior as missing uglify-js. (Only a warning, no error) - The code to load and run uglify is put into a single for readability purposes - Tests use a mockup Module._resolveFilename to simulate the missing module. This function is used by both "require" and "require.resolve", so both are mocked equally.
(cherry picked from commit d5caa56)
